Write a function maxMin that takes an array arr as arguments and returns an array containing the maximum and minimum value: [max, min]. 
If the array is empty return [].

Example:

function maxMin ([3, 4, 8, 1]) should return [8, 1];
function maxMin ([7, 7]) should return [7, 7];
function maxMin ([2]) should return [2, 2];
function maxMin ([]) should return [];

Solution:

function maxMin(arr){
  return arr.length === 0 ? [] : [Math.max(...arr), Math.min(...arr)];
}
